80 grams Sliced Irish Ham
2 unit(s) Baguette
125 grams Mozzarella
55 grams Blue Cheese
1 sachet(s) Balsamic Glaze
1 sachet(s) Cranberry Chutney
tsp Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Cut the baguette widthways at an angle into 2cm slices.
Lay the bread slices onto a baking tray.
Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper.
Toast until golden brown, 8-10 mins.

Once cooked, top half the slices with blue cheese and a drizzle of cranberry chutney.
Tear ham and drained mozzarella over the remaining crostini slices.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.

Serve the crostini on platters.
To finish, drizzle the balsamic glaze over the top.